The paper discusses a control strategy for generating robust gaits for humanoid robots, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The approach proposed in the paper involves decision-making based on feedback from the current state of the robot, which can be categorized as a system-level approach (cs.SY). The approach also involves trajectory generation and optimization, which can be categorized as an artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) approach. Finally, the paper mentions simulation scenarios, which may involve computer vision (cs.CV) techniques for analyzing the results.
